# TradeYa Design System Guidelines

When creating or modifying UI components, ALWAYS follow these TradeYa design system patterns to avoid "AI slop" and maintain consistency.

## Color System

**ALWAYS use TradeYa color tokens, never hardcode colors:**

- **Primary (Orange):** `primary-500` (#f97316), `primary-600`, `primary-400`, etc.
- **Secondary (Blue):** `secondary-500` (#0ea5e9), `secondary-600`, `secondary-400`, etc.
- **Semantic Colors:**
  - Success: `success-500` (#22c55e)
  - Warning: `warning-500` (#f59e0b)
  - Error: `error-500` (#ef4444)
- **Neutral:** `neutral-50` through `neutral-950`

**DO:**
```tsx
<Button className="bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600 text-white">
```

**DON'T:**
```tsx
<Button className="bg-orange-500 hover:bg-orange-600"> // ❌ Hardcoded color
```

## Theme-Aware Classes

**ALWAYS use theme-aware classes for dark mode support:**

**DO:**
```tsx
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100">
```

**DON'T:**
```tsx
<div className="bg-white text-black"> // ❌ No dark mode support
```

## Spacing Scale

**ALWAYS use the 4px base spacing scale:**
- `p-1` = 4px
- `p-2` = 8px
- `p-4` = 16px
- `p-6` = 24px
- `p-8` = 32px

**DO:**
```tsx
<div className="p-4 space-y-4">
```

**DON'T:**
```tsx
<div className="p-5 space-y-3"> // ❌ Not on spacing scale
```

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
**ALWAYS use the Button component with proper variants:**
```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

<Button variant="default">Default</Button>
<Button variant="glassmorphic">Glassmorphic</Button>
<Button variant="premium">Premium</Button>
```

### Cards
**ALWAYS use the Card component:**
```tsx
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/Card';

<Card variant="glass" hover>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>Content</CardContent>
</Card>
```

### Inputs
**ALWAYS use theme-aware Input component:**
```tsx
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/Input';

<Input 
  className="border-glass glassmorphic backdrop-blur-xl"
  placeholder="Enter text"
/>
```

## Glassmorphism Pattern

**For glassmorphic effects, ALWAYS use:**
```tsx
className="glassmorphic border-glass bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm"
```

**DO NOT create custom glassmorphism - use the utility class.**

## Accessibility Requirements

**ALWAYS include:**
- Keyboard navigation support
- ARIA labels where needed
- Focus management
- Screen reader support
- Reduced motion support

**Example:**
```tsx
<button
  aria-label="Close dialog"
  aria-busy={isLoading}
  onKeyDown={(e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
      handleClick();
    }
  }}
>
```

## Component Structure

**ALWAYS follow this pattern:**
1. Import from `@/components/ui/[ComponentName]`
2. Use TypeScript interfaces for props
3. Use `cn()` utility for className merging
4. Include proper TypeScript types
5. Export with proper displayName

**Example:**
```tsx
import { cn } from '@/utils/cn';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

interface MyComponentProps {
  className?: string;
  variant?: 'default' | 'custom';
}

export const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({ 
  className, 
  variant = 'default' 
}) => {
  return (
    <div className={cn(
      'base-classes',
      variant === 'custom' && 'custom-classes',
      className
    )}>
      Content
    </div>
  );
};
```

